title: Residents urged to check yards for girl
text:
Alert: Girl missing from Bellmere The Courier-Mail February 19, 2017 2:57pm SOUTHEAST Queensland residents are being asked to check their backyards for a nine-year-old girl reported missing north of Brisbane. 
The girl was last seen on Seville St, Bellmere, near Caboolture, about 9.30am. 
She is described as Caucasian in appearance, of a slim build with an olive complexion, with blonde shoulder-length hair. 
She was wearing a one-piece black and pink swimming costume with a butterfly on it. 
Police and family have concerns for her welfare due to her age and because she has a medical condition. 
Anyone who sees her is urged to contact police. 
Phone Crime Stoppes on 1800 333 000.
